artshorn, Buckinghamshire, England","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","Monace, Fife, SCOTLAND":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Monace, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called with Old English <i>bere</i> or <i>bær</i> ‘barley’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’, i.e. an outlying grange. Compare   Barwick  . The name is also found in Ireland, where it has been Gaelicized as <b>de Bartún</b>.","Polish (<b>Bartoń</b>); Czech and Slovak (mainly <b>Bartoň</b>): from a pet form of the personal name Polish <i>Bartłomiej</i>, Czech <i>Bartoloměj</i>, Slovak <i>Bartolomej</i>, from Latin <i>Bartholomaeus</i> (see   Bartholomew  ). This surname is also found in Germany."],"variants":[{"name":"Barwick","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Berwick or Barwick, for example in Northumberland, Norfolk, Somerset, and Yorkshire, from Old English <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘outlying farm building’, i.e. a granary lying some distance away from the main settlement.","North German: habitational name from a place called Berwick, near Soest, in Westphalia."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":15,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":24,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":59,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Barton was born about 1200, in Barton Hartshorn, Buckinghamshire, England, his father, Thomas De Barton, was 21 and his mother, Mrs. Cecilia De Barton, was 16. He married Mrs John Barton in 1228, in Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1280, in Fife, Scotland, at the age of 81."},"et":{"about 1200–1280":"umbes 1200–1280","1183–1246":"1183–1246","1200–1236":"1200–1236","1200–1280":"1200–1280","1202–1275":"1202–1275","1230–1305":"1230–1305","1180–1250":"1180–1250","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1275":"1275","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","1183":"1183","1280":"1280","1180":"1180","1228":"1228","Abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1305":"1305","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1202":"1202","1246":"1246","1200":"1200","about 1200":"umbes 1200","Haccomb, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barton Hartshorn, Buckinghamshire, England":"Barton Hartshorn, Buckinghamshire, England","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","Monace, Fife, SCOTLAND":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Monace, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1200–1280":"noin 1200–1280","1183–1246":"1183–1246","1200–1236":"1200–1236","1200–1280":"1200–1280","1202–1275":"1202–1275","1230–1305":"1230–1305","1180–1250":"1180–1250","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1275":"1275","1198